Claimable plot grid around the city + connected road network

The world was a single stretched row with one visible plot and a road that
didn't line up. Reworked it into a proper grid of claimable plots in front
of the city:

- PlotService: PLOT_SLOTS is now a 6x4 grid (24 spots) flanking a central
  avenue, ordered closest-to-city first. New allocateSlot() gives VIP players
  the CLOSEST free slot and free players the FARTHEST — prime spots are a VIP
  perk. Every unclaimed slot shows an "OPEN PLOT" placeholder (lit corner
  posts + floating sign) so the world looks populated and players can see
  where plots are. Slots are freed + the placeholder restored on leave.
- PlotService.initWorld() lays out all placeholders at server start; called
  from Main after the city is built.
- HubService: ground resized/recentred to cover the whole grid + city; roads
  rebuilt as a central avenue (city gate -> back of grid) plus an east-west
  cross street at every plot row, so near and far plots all drive to centre.

